text: Téteghem-Coudekerque-Village (; ; ) is a commune in the Nord in north France. In 2019, 8,285 people lived there. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Téteghem (the seat) and Coudekerque-Village.Arrêté préfectoral 30 November 2015 == Other websites == * INSEE commune file ==References== Category:Communes in Nord Category:2016 establishments in France
